    'techOverview.section5.itemInstrumentIntegration.title': "Direct Medical Instrument Integration",
    'techOverview.section5.itemInstrumentIntegration.desc': "Ability to automatically read and import data from electronic hospital instruments (e.g., vital signs monitors for body temperature, blood pressure; laboratory analyzers for results; imaging equipment for DICOM data), reducing manual entry and errors.",
    'techOverview.section5.itemBiomedicalEngineering.title': "Biomedical Engineering Module",
    'techOverview.section5.itemBiomedicalEngineering.desc': "A dedicated module for managing medical equipment, including inventory, maintenance schedules, fault reporting, calibration records, and tracking equipment utilization to ensure operational readiness and compliance.",
    'techOverview.section5.itemAdvancedReporting.title': "Advanced Reporting & Analytics (Hierarchical)",
    'techOverview.section5.itemAdvancedReporting.desc': "Development of the Reporting module to include advanced data visualization, customizable report generation, trend analysis, and export functionalities. Reports will be tailored for different hierarchical levels (hospital, district, provincial, national) to support administrative and clinical decision-making. Authorized healthcare professionals will have nationwide access to a patient's complete medical history for direct care continuity.",
    'techOverview.section5.itemCampaignManagement.title': "Health Campaign Management",
    'techOverview.section5.itemCampaignManagement.desc': "Full development of the Campaigns module to support planning, execution, resource allocation, progress tracking, and outcome analysis of public health initiatives such as vaccination drives or health awareness programs.",
    'techOverview.section5.itemWarehouseManagement.title': "Dedicated Warehouse Management Module",
    'techOverview.section5.itemWarehouseManagement.desc': "Implementation of a centralized warehouse module to manage stock levels for both pharmacy and laboratory supplies across hierarchical levels (hospital, district, provincial, national). This includes automated replenishment requests, stock tracking, expiry date management, and distribution logistics.",
    'techOverview.section5.itemSecurityCompliance.title': "Security & Compliance",
    'techOverview.section5.itemSecurityCompliance.desc': "Rigorous implementation of security best practices and adherence to relevant data privacy regulations (e.g., HIPAA, GDPR, or specific Mozambican data protection laws). This includes robust audit trails to track all access to patient data, strong encryption, and mechanisms to ensure that nationwide clinical access to patient records is legitimate, secure, and compliant.",
    'techOverview.section5.itemUserRoles.title': "User Roles & Permissions with Hierarchical Access and Nationwide Clinical Record Access",
    'techOverview.section5.itemUserRoles.desc': "A granular system for defining user roles (doctor, nurse, admin, lab tech, etc.) with specific permissions. Authorized healthcare professionals (doctors, nurses, specialists) will have nationwide access to a patient's complete medical history for direct care continuity, regardless of treatment location. Administrative and reporting access will be hierarchical (hospital, district, provincial, national) to view and manage aggregated data and operational information relevant to their scope.",
    'techOverview.section5.itemOffline.title': "Offline Capabilities",
    'techOverview.section5.itemOffline.desc': "Development of features that allow the application to function in areas with intermittent or no internet connectivity, with data synchronization when connectivity is restored, crucial for remote or underserved areas.",
    'techOverview.section5.itemI18nFull.title': "Full Internationalization (i18n)",
    'techOverview.section5.itemI18nFull.desc': "Complete translation of all application text and adaptation of formats (dates, numbers) to support multiple languages and regional preferences for nationwide deployment, ensuring accessibility for all users.",
    'techOverview.section5.itemPatientPortal.title': "Patient Portal & Mobile Engagement",
    'techOverview.section5.itemPatientPortal.desc': "Development of a patient-facing portal and mobile application. Patients would be able to securely access their own medical information using their National ID or Passport number. Features would include viewing appointments, lab results, medical history, and educational materials.",
    'techOverview.section5.itemMedicationAdherence.title': "Medication Adherence & Reminders",
    'techOverview.section5.itemMedicationAdherence.desc': "Integration of in-app notifications and reminders sent directly to patients for medication administration. Patients would be able to confirm medication intake, providing valuable data for adherence tracking and allowing healthcare providers to monitor compliance (e.g., confirming each dose for a medication prescribed three times a day).",
    'techOverview.section5.itemBilling.title': "Billing and Financial Management",
    'techOverview.section5.itemBilling.desc': "Comprehensive module for managing patient billing, generating invoices, processing payments (cash, card, mobile money, insurance), managing insurance claims, tracking accounts receivable, and financial reporting for hospital services. This would also include tariff management for different services and patient categories.",
    'techOverview.section5.itemTelemedicine.title': "Telemedicine Module",
    'techOverview.section5.itemTelemedicine.desc': "Functionality for conducting secure remote video consultations, allowing doctors to connect with patients who cannot easily visit the hospital. This would include features for scheduling tele-appointments, sharing necessary documents securely, and integrating with digital prescription capabilities.",
    'techOverview.section5.itemAdvancedAnalyticsBI.title': "Advanced Analytics and Business Intelligence (BI)",
    'techOverview.section5.itemAdvancedAnalyticsBI.desc': "Beyond standard reporting, this involves tools for in-depth data analysis, creating customizable dashboards for hospital management, predictive analytics for resource planning (e.g., forecasting patient load, supply needs), and identifying trends in public health or operational efficiency.",
    'techOverview.section5.itemBloodBank.title': "Blood Bank Management",
